9 ASSOCIATION ACT, TO CLARIFY INSURANCE REBATE PERMITTED TRADE
10 PRACTICES, TO CLARIFY THE LAWS RELATING TO THE EXCHANGE OF
11 BUSINESS BETWEEN INSURANCE PRODUCERS, TO REQUIRE DRIVERS SUBJECT
12 TO THE INEXPERIENCED DRIVER PREMIUM SURCHARGE TO MAINTAIN OR
13 BENEFIT FROM CONTINUOUS LIABILITY COVERAGE, TO PLACE
14 RESTRICTIONS ON RESIDENTIAL LEASES REQUIRING RENTERS INSURANCE,
15 TO MAKE CHANGES TO THE EFFECTIVE DATE OF CERTAIN PROVISIONS
16 CONCERNING THE CALCULATION OF UNDERINSURED MOTORIST COVERAGE
17 AND INSURANCE RATEMAKING LAWS IN S.L. 2023-133, AS AMENDED BY S.L.
18 2024-29, TO AUTHORIZE SALESMEN TO REGISTER WITH MULTIPLE DEALERS
19 UNDER COMMON OWNERSHIP OR CONTROL, AND TO AUTHORIZE POLICY
20 CANCELLATION UPON CHARGEBACK OF A CREDIT CARD PREMIUM
21 PAYMENT.
