15 PART II. CLARIFY INSURANCE FEE REFERRAL CAP
16 SECTION 2.(a) G.S. 58-33-82(f) reads as rewritten:
17 "(f) No commission, fee, or other valuable consideration authorized under subsection (e)
18 of this section for the referral of insurance business by an unlicensed individual to a licensed
19 insurance agent or broker producer licensed under G.S. 58-33-26(c1)(6) shall exceed fifty dollars
20 ($50.00) in value. A violation of this subsection may be punished by a fine not to exceed two
21 thousand dollars ($2,000) for each violation. This subsection shall not apply to title insurance."
22 SECTION 2.(b) This section becomes effective October 1, 2025, and applies to any
23 referral of personal lines insurance business made on or after that date.
