26 IV. The drawing or raffle is open to the public and
27 conducted in a manner that is not unfairly
28 discriminatory.
29 V. The customer is not required to purchase, continue to
30 purchase, or renew a policy in exchange for
31 participation in the drawing or raffle.
32 c. No insurer or employee thereof, and no insurance producer shall pay,
33 allow, or give, or offer to pay, allow, or give, directly or indirectly, as
34 an inducement to insurance, or after insurance has been effected, any
35 rebate, discount, abatement, credit or reduction of the premium named
36 in a policy of insurance, or any special favor or advantage in the
37 dividends or other benefits to accrue thereon, or any valuable
38 consideration or inducement whatever, not specified in the policy of
39 insurance. Nothing herein contained shall be construed as prohibiting
40 prohibiting: (i) the payment of commissions or other compensation to
41 regularly appointed and licensed insurance producers duly licensed by
42 this State; nor as prohibiting State, (ii) any participating insurer from
43 distributing to its policyholders dividends, savings or the unused or
44 unabsorbed portion of premiums and premium deposits.deposits, or
45 (iii) the trade practices permitted by sub-subdivision b. of this
46 subdivision.
47 d. An insurer, producer, or representative of either may not offer or
48 provide insurance as an inducement to the purchase of another policy
49 or otherwise use the words "free," "no cost," or words of similar import
50 about the policy sale or purchase, in an advertisement. The prohibition
51 on the use of the words "free" and "no cost" in this sub-subdivision
