7 SECTION 7.(c) Article 33 of Chapter 58 of the General Statutes is amended by
8 adding a new section to read:
9 "§ 58-33-82.1. Exchange of business.
10 (a) Producers may exchange business, and split the commission involved with that
11 business, if the producer forwarding the business and the producer receiving the business both:
12 (1) Are licensed in all lines of insurance involved in the exchange and appointed
13 as required by this Article.
14 (2) Sign or include their National Producer Numbers on the insurer's insurance
15 application and provide written or electronic notice to the insurer and
16 consumer of the business exchange.
17 (3) Have a good-faith belief that the exchange of business complies with the
18 requirements of this Article.
19 (b) This section does not limit:
20 (1) The exchange of business in connection with specialty lines or nonstandard
21 and professional liability business that is either:
22 a. Placed through a surplus lines producer; or
23 b. Written at an excess rate or on an individually rated and risked basis.
24 (2) The exchange of business in connection with risk sharing plans."
25 SECTION 7.(d) This section is effective when it becomes law and applies to
26 contracts entered into or renewed on or after that date.
